custom-block.comment: "square" is a specific block we have made to simplify this code. "Right click" on it and select "edit" to have look inside.

block.comment: The "turn" block combined with the subdivison operator is great to be used for repeated elements in a circle. The 360 degrees are divided by the number of repetitions. Try to change that.

Try to execute the code also without this block. It changes the pattern in the center. For embroidery it is important to not overlap stitches more than about 10 times. This block moves away from the center point and therefore makes it possible to repeat the "squares" more often.
